---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

const PHONE = '(805) 341-4121';
const PHONE_LINK = 'tel:+18053414121';
const EMAIL = 'alohawindowbros@gmail.com';
const EMAIL_LINK = `mailto:${EMAIL}`;
const CALENDLY = 'https://calendly.com/alohawindowbros-r6nn/30min?hide_gdpr_banner=1';
const EFFECTIVE_DATE = 'May 3, 2026';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | Aloha Window Bros"
  description="How Aloha Window Bros collects, uses, and protects information when you use our website or request a quote for window cleaning services in Ventura County."
>
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="blog-post-hero">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <time datetime="2026-05-03">Last updated: {EFFECTIVE_DATE}</time>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="service-content-section">
    <article class="service-article">
      <div class="article-content">
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Aloha Window Bros</strong>
          ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects information when
          you visit <a href="https://alohawindowbros.com">alohawindowbros.com</a>
          (the "Site") or request a quote for window cleaning, screen cleaning,
          or solar panel cleaning services in Ventura County, California.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're a locally owned home services business — not a tech company —
          and we keep this policy in plain English so you can actually read it.
          By using our Site or services, you agree to the practices described
          below.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
          Aloha Window Bros is a window cleaning company serving homeowners and
          businesses across Ventura County, California, including Thousand
          Oaks, Westlake Village, Agoura Hills, Newbury Park, Camarillo,
          Ventura, Oxnard, Simi Valley, and surrounding areas. You can reach us
          using the contact information at the bottom of this policy.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>Information you provide to us</h3>
        <p>
          When you request a quote, schedule a service, or contact us, you may
          give us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your name</li>
          <li>Phone number</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Service address (so we know where to come)</li>
          <li>Details about the property and the work you want done</li>
          <li>
            Any other information you choose to share in a message, form, or
            scheduling tool
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
        <p>
          When you visit the Site, certain information is collected
          automatically by analytics and advertising tools, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>IP address and approximate geographic location</li>
          <li>Browser type, operating system, and device type</li>
          <li>Pages visited, time on page, and referring URL</li>
          <li>Date and time of access</li>
          <li>Interactions such as button clicks, form submissions, and scroll behavior</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Cookies and tracking technologies</h3>
        <p>
          The Site uses cookies, pixels, and similar technologies — most
          notably Google Analytics 4 and the Meta (Facebook) Pixel — to
          understand how the Site is used and to measure the effectiveness of
          our advertising. See sections 5, 6, and 7 below for details and how
          to opt out.
        </p>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Respond to quote requests and questions</li>
          <li>Schedule, perform, and follow up on services</li>
          <li>Send appointment confirmations and reminders</li>
          <li>Process payments and keep records of jobs we've completed</li>
          <li>Improve the Site, our services, and customer experience</li>
          <li>
            Measure how our website and ads perform, including which pages and
            campaigns lead to quote requests
          </li>
          <li>
            Show ads to people who have visited our Site or who look similar to
            our existing customers (retargeting and lookalike audiences) on
            Meta and Google platforms
          </li>
          <li>
            Comply with legal obligations and enforce our terms and agreements
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Share Information</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>We do not sell your personal information.</strong> We share
          information only with the people and services we need to run the
          business:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Service providers</strong> — companies that help us
            operate, including our scheduling tool (Calendly), email and
            messaging providers, payment processors, customer relationship
            management (CRM) tools, and website hosting.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Advertising and analytics partners</strong> — Meta
            Platforms, Inc. (Facebook/Instagram) and Google LLC (Google
            Analytics, Google Ads), which receive certain data through pixels
            and tags on the Site so we can measure performance and reach
            people who may want our services.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal and safety</strong> — we may disclose information if
            required by law, subpoena, or court order, or if we believe in
            good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect rights, safety,
            or property.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Business transfers</strong> — if Aloha Window Bros is ever
            sold, merged, or reorganized, customer information may be
            transferred as part of that transaction.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Meta (Facebook &amp; Instagram) Advertising</h2>
        <p>
          Our website uses the <strong>Meta Pixel</strong> (ID
          2085643305314161). The Pixel is a small piece of code from Meta that
          loads on each page of the Site. It allows us to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Measure the results of our Facebook and Instagram ads</li>
          <li>
            See which pages people visit after clicking an ad and whether they
            request a quote
          </li>
          <li>
            Show ads on Facebook and Instagram to people who have visited our
            Site (this is called <em>retargeting</em>)
          </li>
          <li>
            Build <em>Custom Audiences</em> from website visitors and customer
            lists, and create <em>Lookalike Audiences</em> of people similar
            to our existing customers
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Information shared with Meta through the Pixel can include your IP
          address, browser/device information, the pages you viewed on our
          Site, and actions you took (like clicking a phone number or quote
          button). Meta uses this information under its own
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/policy.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Data Policy</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can control how Meta uses your data for advertising in your
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/adpreferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Facebook Ad Preferences</a>
          or
          <a href="https://www.instagram.com/accounts/privacy_and_security/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Instagram privacy settings</a>.
          You can also opt out of interest-based advertising industry-wide at
          <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">optout.aboutads.info</a>
          and
          <a href="https://www.networkadvertising.org/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">networkadvertising.org/choices</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Google Analytics &amp; Google Ads</h2>
        <p>
          We use <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> (measurement ID
          G-MRSP8D9CQG) to understand how visitors use the Site. Google
          Analytics collects information such as the pages you view, how long
          you spend on the Site, the type of device and browser you use, and
          your approximate location based on IP address. We may also use
          Google Ads remarketing to show ads on Google's network to people who
          have visited the Site.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking by installing the
          official
          <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-Out Browser Add-on</a>,
          and you can manage Google ad personalization at
          <a href="https://adssettings.google.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">adssettings.google.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files stored on your device. The Site uses:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Essential cookies</strong> needed for the Site to load and
            function properly
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics cookies</strong> (Google Analytics) to measure
            traffic and usage
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Advertising cookies</strong> (Meta Pixel, Google Ads) to
            measure and personalize ads
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Most browsers let you block or delete cookies in their settings. If
          you block cookies, parts of the Site may not work as well.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        <p>
          You can ask us, at any time, to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Confirm what personal information we hold about you</li>
          <li>Correct information that's inaccurate</li>
          <li>Delete information we no longer need to keep</li>
          <li>Stop sending you marketing messages</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To make a request, email us at
          <a href={EMAIL_LINK}>{EMAIL}</a> or call <a href={PHONE_LINK}>{PHONE}</a>.
          We'll respond within a reasonable timeframe.
        </p>

        <h3>California residents (CCPA / CPRA)</h3>
        <p>
          If you live in California, the California Consumer Privacy Act gives
          you specific rights in addition to the ones above, including the
          right to know what personal information we collect, the right to
          request deletion of that information, and the right to opt out of
          the "sale" or "sharing" of personal information for cross-context
          behavioral advertising.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not sell personal information for money. However, the use of
          advertising pixels (such as the Meta Pixel and Google Ads tags) may
          be considered "sharing" under the CPRA. To opt out of this kind of
          sharing, email
          <a href={EMAIL_LINK}>{EMAIL}</a>
          with the subject line
          <em>"Do Not Share My Personal Information"</em>, or use the opt-out
          tools listed in sections 5 and 6.
        </p>

        <h3>Visitors from outside the U.S. (GDPR)</h3>
        <p>
          We primarily serve customers in California. If you visit the Site
          from the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or another
          jurisdiction with similar privacy laws, our legal basis for
          processing your information is your consent (for analytics and
          advertising cookies), our legitimate interest in operating and
          improving the Site, and where applicable the performance of a
          contract (when you book a service). You may also have the right to
          lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use reasonable physical, technical, and administrative measures
          to protect the information we collect — including secure hosting,
          HTTPS encryption on the Site, and limited access to customer
          records. No method of transmission or storage on the internet is
          ever 100% secure, however, and we can't guarantee absolute
          security.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our services and Site are intended for adults. We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe
          a child has provided us with personal information, please contact
          us and we will delete it.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          The Site may link to third-party sites we don't operate, such as
          Google Maps, Calendly, or our social media profiles. We're not
          responsible for the privacy practices of those sites; please review
          their policies separately.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time as our business
          or the law changes. When we do, we'll post the updated version here
          with a new "Last updated" date at the top. Continued use of the
          Site after an update means you accept the revised policy.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, concerns, or requests about this policy or your
          information? Reach out and we'll get back to you:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Aloha Window Bros</strong></li>
          <li>Phone: <a href={PHONE_LINK}>{PHONE}</a></li>
          <li>Email: <a href={EMAIL_LINK}>{EMAIL}</a></li>
          <li>Website: <a href="https://alohawindowbros.com">alohawindowbros.com</a></li>
          <li>Service area: Ventura County, California</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Sidebar -->
    <aside class="service-sidebar">
      <div class="sidebar-card">
        <h3>Need a Free Quote?</h3>
        <p>Schedule online or call — we'll come to you.</p>
        <a href={CALENDLY} class="hero-cta-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="width:100%;text-align:center;">Schedule Now</a>
        <div class="sidebar-divider"><span>or</span></div>
        <a href={PHONE_LINK} class="sidebar-phone">{PHONE}</a>
      </div>

      <div class="sidebar-card sidebar-services">
        <h4>Our Services</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/services/window-washing">Window Washing</a></li>
          <li><a href="/services/screen-cleaning">Screen Cleaning</a></li>
          <li><a href="/services/solar-panel-cleaning">Solar Panel Cleaning</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="sidebar-card sidebar-guarantee">
        <div class="sidebar-guarantee-icon">⭐</div>
        <h4>100% Satisfaction Guarantee</h4>
        <p>We walk the property with you before we leave. Not happy? We redo it on the spot.</p>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Base>
